
====================================================================================================
SELECTED SALAD RECIPES LIST (TAKEN FROM A COMPREHENSIVE LIST)
====================================================================================================

For each category recipes are ranked in order from highest to lowest

Green Salads: 
    #1 - Herb Salad — parsley, mint, basil, and chervil mixed with tender greens for a fragrant, delicate salad.
    #2 - Radicchio Salad — bitter radicchio balanced with sweet or creamy elements like honey, balsamic, or gorgonzola.
    #3 - Kale Salad (Massaged Kale or Kale Caesar) — hearty kale leaves tenderized and dressed with bold vinaigrettes.
    #4 - Wedge Salad — iceberg wedge topped with blue cheese dressing, bacon, tomato, and chives.
    #5 - Escarole Salad — slightly bitter escarole paired with anchovy, lemon, or Parmesan.
    #6 - Frisée aux Lardons (Lyonnaise Salad) — frisée with bacon lardons, croutons, and a poached egg.

Vegetable Salads: 
    #8 - Warm lentil and roasted vegetable salad — hearty base of lentils paired with roast veg and vinaigrette (legumes + veg)
    #9 - Russian vinaigrette — diced beets, potatoes, carrots, pickles, and sauerkraut or peas dressed with oil and vinegar.
    #10 - Beet and goat cheese salad — roasted or boiled beets with tangy cheese, nuts, and vinaigrette.
    #11 - Ratatouille salad — roasted Mediterranean vegetables (eggplant, zucchini, bell pepper, tomato) served room temperature with herbs.
    #5 - Coleslaw (classic and variations) — shredded cabbage with mayonnaise or vinegar-based dressing; many regional variants.

Legume/Bean Salads: 
    #12 - French Lentil Salad (Salade de Lentilles du Puy) — peppery Puy lentils with shallot vinaigrette, herbs, sometimes bacon.
    #13 - Warm Lentil and Bacon/Vegetable Salad — lentils tossed warm with soft vegetables or lardons and mustard vinaigrette.
    #14 - Niçoise with Beans (haricots verts &/or white beans) — composed salad where beans are a primary structural element.
    #15 - Smoky Bean Salad with Charred Vegetables and Romesco — grilled veg and beans finished with a nutty red pepper sauce.
    #16 - Gigantes Salad (Greek Giant Bean Salad) — boiled gigantes (large white beans) tossed simply with tomato, onion, and oregano.
    #17 - Balela (Levantine Black Bean/Chickpea Salad) — chickpeas and/or black beans with tomatoes, parsley, cumin, and lemon.
    #18 - Puy Lentil and Goat Cheese Salad — peppery lentils balanced with creamy cheese and sharp vinaigrette.

Pasta Salads: 
    #19 - Mediterranean Orzo Salad — orzo with cucumber, tomato, red onion, feta, olives, and lemon olive oil dressing.
    #20 - Asian Cold Noodle Salad (wheat pasta / somen style crossover) — wheat pasta with sesame, soy, rice vinegar, scallion, cucumber, and chili oil.
    #21 - Cavatappi with Broccoli and Sundried Tomatoes — toothsome pasta with blanched broccoli, sundried tomatoes, olives, and a sharp vinaigrette.
    #22 - Pasta Niçoise Salad — fusilli or penne with green beans, potatoes, olives, tomatoes, and tuna or boiled eggs, dressed in vinaigrette.
    #23 - Cold Carbonara-style Pasta Salad — pasta with pancetta or bacon, pea, shaved pecorino, and a loose, bright dressing inspired by carbonara ingredients.
    #24 - Creamy Avocado Pasta Salad — pasta tossed with avocado based creamy dressing, lime, cilantro, and crisp veggies.

Grain Salads: 
    #25 - Sorghum Salad — toothsome sorghum with roasted peppers, beans, and bold vinaigrette.
    #26 - Wild Rice Salad — nutty wild rice with dried fruit, nuts, celery, and a citrusy dressing.
    #27 - Freekeh Salad — smoky green wheat used cold or warm with pomegranate, herbs, and spiced dressing.
    #28 - Greek-style Grain Salad (farro or barley with cucumber, tomato, olives, feta) — classic Mediterranean flavors on a chewy grain base.
    #29 - Korean-style Cold Grain Bowls (multigrain or barley with pickled veg) — chilled grains with tangy, spicy banchan components.
    #30 - Bulgur Salad (Koofteh / simple cracked wheat variants) — quick bulgur salads distinct from tabbouleh, often with tomato and cucumber.

Mixed Protein Salads: 
    #31 - Niçoise Salad — composed salad with tuna (or anchovy), hard boiled egg, potatoes, green beans, olives.
    #32 - Cobb Salad — chopped greens topped with grilled chicken, bacon, hard boiled egg, avocado, tomato, blue cheese.
    #33 - Warm Steak and Shrimp Salad (surf and turf salad) — sliced grilled steak paired with seared shrimp over peppery greens and warm vinaigrette.
    #34 - Antipasto Salad — Italian style platter salad with salumi, fresh/provolone cheeses, marinated vegetables, olives.

Fruit Salad: 
    #35 - Poached Pear Salad — pears poached in wine or spiced syrup, served chilled with nuts and cheese.
    #36 - Persian Fruit Salad (Faloodeh style elements) — seasonal fruit with rosewater, lime, and chopped pistachio.
    #37 - Grilled Fruit Salad — charred peaches, pineapple, or figs with honey, yogurt, or mascarpone.
    #38 - Strawberry Spinach Salad (fruit + greens crossover) — strawberries, baby spinach, nuts, and a poppyseed or balsamic dressing.
    #39 - Fig and Prosciutto Salad — fresh figs, prosciutto, arugula, and a honey balsamic finish.
    #40 - Salade de Fruits à la Vanille (Vanilla scented fruit salad) — mixed fruit lightly macerated with vanilla and citrus.
    #41 - Greek Yogurt and Fruit Parfait Salad — layered fruit with yogurt, granola, and a honey drizzle.
    #42 - Fruit Salsa — diced mango, pineapple, and strawberry with lime and jalapeño; served with chips or fish.

